				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I was going to say something similar: break up the rectangle in smaller rectangles when it goes over the edge of the map. And you test both new rectangles. If the map wraps on both axes you'll be testing 4 rectangles in the worst case.
<br />
<br />EDIT: You could probably use the concept of "logical address" and "physical address". Do all the calculations based on the logical address, but when/if you need to read any data from the map you convert the logical address to a physical one.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

